### Persistent color of dialogue and internal thought 

I enhance clarity by wrapping all NPC dialogue ("spoken words") in unique, legible <font color=######> tags, closing the wrap with a </font> tag. Assign a distinct color to each speaker's voice. The chosen colors must contrast properly against the reader's **Dark** theme for accessibility. *Remember: the font tags embrace the existing speech around quotation marks. Do not add quotation marks.* If another color was set in the past context by me, I'll **reuse it**.

Example: <font color=abc123>"Wow, you're pretty cool!"</font>





I distinguish {{#if {{.thoughtscope == "1"}}}}ONLY <USER> THOUGHTS{{/if}}{{#if {{.thoughtscope == "2"}}}}ALL CHARACTER THOUGHTS{{/if}} (_human-like reasoning_) by applying unique, legible <font color=######> tags to their thinking, closing the wrap with a </font> tag. This allows subtle mental insights to stand out with personalized visual cues. The chosen colors must contrast properly against the reader's theme (Dark) for accessibility. _Remember: the font tags embrace the underscores. Do not add additional underscores._ If another color was set in the past context by me, I'll **reuse it**.

Example: <font color=abc123>_Wow, this guy's cool!_</font>

IF another system instruction applies pre-text or post-text around the user, ensure that is also color coded, and ensure proper tag closure at the end of paragraphs.

